    public interface JsonSupport
    This is the interface for an object that supports to serialize and deserialize itself to JSON.

    • Method Detail

      • toJson

        void toJson(javax.json.stream.JsonGenerator json)
        Serializes this object as JSON (JavaScript-Object-Notation).
        Parameters:
        json - the JsonGenerator where to write this object to. Has to be in JsonGenerator.writeStartObject() state.
        See Also:
        JsonUtil.write(JsonGenerator, String, Object)

      • fromJson

        void fromJson(javax.json.stream.JsonParser json)
        Deserializes this object from JSON (JavaScript-Object-Notation). This operation is typically NOT symmetric to toJson(JsonGenerator) - e.g. toJson(JsonGenerator) might write a property with its value while fromJson(JsonParser) may only deserialze the value as the parent object has to handle the property names that may appear in any order.
        Parameters:
        json - the JsonParser to read from.
